China’s Power Capacity to Rise 77% by 2020, State Grid Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-20T08:25:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/china-s-power-capacity-to-rise-77-by-2020-state-grid-says.html
China ’s power generation capacity
will rise 77 percent by the end of this decade, according to a
research director at the nation’s largest electricity
distributor.  The nation’s power capacity will climb to 1.7 billion
kilowatts by 2020, the largest in the world, with coal
accounting for 59 percent of generation, Yang Yingjian, chief
engineer at State Grid Corp. of China’s  research institute , said
at a conference in Shanghai today. China’s power generation
capacity totaled 962 million kilowatts as of last year,
according to the China Electricity Council.  Power capacity may rise to 1.44 billion kilowatts by 2015
and electricity demand is expected to climb to 6.1 trillion
kilowatt-hours, Yang said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helen Sun in  Shanghai  at 
 hsun30@bloomberg.net 
